overview: The user wanted to improve the visual appeal of their sleep
  questionnaire app, which they felt was too generic. The assistant conducted a
  detailed aesthetic analysis, identifying areas for improvement in color,
  typography, spacing, form elements, and overall visual interest. A new,
  calming sleep-themed color palette was introduced, and the main form layout
  was enhanced with decorative elements and a redesigned progress indicator. Key
  sections like the Intro and Report were given a more polished look, and all
  core UI components, including checkboxes, radio buttons, and sliders, were
  updated for better visual feedback and consistency. The changes aimed to
  create a more professional and engaging experience, moving away from a
  template-driven design. The code changes were successfully applied and
  compiled, though a full visual verification in the browser was partially
  hampered by tool limitations.
